node.title: Queensland hits 80 per cent COVID vaccination milestone, but it's no 'Freedom Day'
node.alt: A health worker with a needle.
node.description: The vaccination target for those 16 and over was reached more than a week early, however the state will not open its borders to hotpots until Monday.
node.content:
["Queensland has reached\u00a0an 80 per cent COVID-19 vaccination milestone, more than a week ahead of schedule.", "Prime Minister Scott Morrison announced\u00a0this morning that 80 per cent of Queenslanders 16 and over had\u00a0now received two vaccine doses\u00a0and Premier Annastacia Palaszczuk confirmed the news soon after.", "\"Very few places in the world have got to this level of protection before a COVID-19 wave arrives,\" Ms Palaszczuk tweeted.", "\"The credit for this belongs to each and every Queenslander.\"", "The target \u2014\u00a0for\u00a0Queenslanders over 16 having had two doses \u2014\u00a0was deemed to be the trigger for Queensland to relax border restrictions.", "Earlier this week, Ms Palaszczuk said it was clear the state would pass the 80 per cent mark this week and announced the state would be the reopening at 1:00am Monday.", "The exact vaccination rate is expected to be publicly released later today.", "
No 'Freedom Day'
", "Mater Health Services director of infectious diseases Paul Griffin said although interstate borders were about to reopen, Queenslanders should not view it as \"Freedom Day\".", "", "
When COVID restrictions were dropped in Britain, people celebrated with parties. Queenslanders should not expect all rules to end soon.(AP:\u00a0Alberto Pezzali)
", "On July 19, the British Government lifted most of its COVID-19 restrictions, triggering \"Freedom Day\" parties across the country, with revellers celebrating at reopened nightclubs.", "Overnight, Britain announced new measures to curb the spread of the virus.", "Dr Griffin said Queensland was not about to \"abandon all of our restrictions and essentially try to pretend we're through COVID\".", "\"We're still going to have testing, we're still going to have social distancing, we're still going to have to check-in,\" he said.", "\"We're still going to ask positive cases to isolate until they're well and not infectious, thereby reducing the prospects for their transmission.\"", "Dr Griffin, an associate professor at the University of Queensland, did not expect \"a huge spike in cases immediately\" once borders reopen.", "\"I think it will trickle in,\" he said.", "\"We're one of the most vaccinated countries in the world, one of the most recently vaccinated countries in the world. We're opening up at a higher rate than most others and we are going to continue those other strategies.", "\"We should all be optimistic for reasonable levels of control.", "\"The main thing is not to be complacent and it would still be great if we could get our double vaccination rate to the 90s like the ACT, Victoria and NSW have.\""]
